quran[73]{c,v,t}:
  33,1,"O Prophet! ňĻAlwaysňļ be mindful of Allah, and do not yield to the disbelievers and the hypocrites. Indeed, Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  33,2,Follow what is revealed to you from your Lord. Surely Allah is All-Aware of what you ňĻallňļ do
  33,3,"And put your trust in Allah, for Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  33,4,"Allah does not place two hearts in any person‚Äôs chest. Nor does He regard your wives as ňĻunlawful for you likeňļ your real mothers, ňĻevenňļ if you say they are.¬†Nor does He regard your adopted children as your real children.¬†These are only your baseless assertions. But Allah declares the truth, and He ňĻaloneňļ guides to the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  33,5,"Let your adopted children keep their family names. That is more just in the sight of Allah. But if you do not know their fathers, then they are ňĻsimplyňļ your fellow believers and close associates. There is no blame on you for what you do by mistake, but ňĻonlyňļ for what you do intentionally. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,6,"The Prophet has a stronger affinity to the believers than they do themselves. And his wives are their mothers. As ordained by Allah, blood relatives are more entitled ňĻto inheritanceňļ than ňĻotherňļ believers and immigrants, unless you ňĻwant toňļ show kindness to your ňĻcloseňļ associates ňĻthrough bequestňļ.¬†This is decreed in the Record"
  33,7,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took a covenant from the prophets, as well as from you ňĻO Prophetňļ, and from Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, son of Mary. We did take a solemn covenant from ňĻall ofňļ them"
  33,8,so that He may question these men of truth about their ňĻdelivery of theňļ truth. And He has prepared a painful punishment for the disbelievers
  33,9,"O believers! Remember Allah‚Äôs favour upon you when ňĻenemyňļ forces came to ňĻbesiegeňļ you ňĻin Medinaňļ,¬†so We sent against them a ňĻbitterňļ wind and forces you could not see.¬†And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  33,10,"ňĻRememberňļ when they came at you from east and west,¬†when your eyes grew wild ňĻin horrorňļ and your hearts jumped into your throats, and you entertained ňĻconflictingňļ thoughts about Allah"
  33,11,"Then and there the believers were put to the test, and were violently shaken"
  33,12,"And ňĻrememberňļ when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, ‚ÄúAllah and His Messenger have promised us nothing but delusion!‚ÄĚ"
  33,13,"And ňĻrememberňļ when a group of them said, ‚ÄúO people of Yathrib!¬†There is no point in you staying ňĻhereňļ, so retreat!‚ÄĚ Another group of them asked the Prophet‚Äôs permission ňĻto leaveňļ, saying, ‚ÄúOur homes are vulnerable,‚ÄĚ while ňĻin factňļ they were not vulnerable. They only wished to flee"
  33,14,"Had their city been sacked from all sides and they had been asked to abandon faith, they would have done so with little hesitation"
  33,15,They had already pledged to Allah earlier never to turn their backs ňĻin retreatňļ. And a pledge to Allah must be answered for
  33,16,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúFleeing will not benefit you if you ňĻtry toňļ escape a natural or violent death. ňĻIf it is not your time,ňļ you will only be allowed enjoyment for a little while.‚ÄĚ"
  33,17,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho can put you out of Allah‚Äôs reach if He intends to harm you or show you mercy?‚ÄĚ They can never find any protector or helper besides Allah"
  33,18,"Allah knows well those among you who discourage ňĻothers from fightingňļ, saying ňĻsecretlyňļ to their brothers, ‚ÄúStay with us,‚ÄĚ and who themselves hardly take part in fighting"
  33,19,"ňĻThey areňļ totally unwilling to assist you. When danger comes, you see them staring at you with their eyes rolling like someone in the throes of death. But once the danger is over, they slash you with razor-sharp tongues, ravenous for ňĻworldlyňļ gains. Such people have not ňĻtrulyňļ believed, so Allah has rendered their deeds void. And that is easy for Allah"
  33,20,"They ňĻstillňļ think that the enemy alliance has not ňĻyetňļ withdrawn. And if the allies were to come ňĻagainňļ, the hypocrites would wish to be away in the desert among nomadic Arabs, ňĻonlyňļ asking for news about you ňĻbelieversňļ. And if the hypocrites were in your midst, they would hardly take part in the fight"
  33,21,"Indeed, in the Messenger of Allah you have an excellent example for whoever has hope in Allah and the Last Day, and remembers Allah often"
  33,22,"When the believers saw the enemy alliance, they said, ‚ÄúThis is what Allah and His Messenger had promised us. The promise of Allah and His Messenger has come true.‚ÄĚ And this only increased them in faith and submission"
  33,23,"Among the believers are men who have proven true to what they pledged to Allah.¬†Some of them have fulfilled their pledge ňĻwith their livesňļ, others are waiting ňĻtheir turnňļ. They have never changed ňĻtheir commitmentňļ in the least"
  33,24,"ňĻIt all happenedňļ so Allah may reward the faithful for their faithfulness, and punish the hypocrites if He wills or turn to them ňĻin mercyňļ. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,25,"And Allah drove back the disbelievers in their rage, totally empty-handed. And Allah spared the believers from fighting. For Allah is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  33,26,"And He brought down those from the People of the Book¬†who supported the enemy alliance from their own strongholds, and cast horror into their hearts. You ňĻbelieversňļ killed some, and took others captive"
  33,27,"He has also caused you to take over their lands, homes, and wealth, as well as lands you have not yet set foot on. And Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  33,28,"O Prophet! Say to your wives, ‚ÄúIf you desire the life of this world and its luxury, then come, I will give you a ňĻsuitableňļ compensation ňĻfor divorceňļ and let you go graciously"
  33,29,"But if you desire Allah and His Messenger and the ňĻeverlastingňļ Home of the Hereafter, then Surely Allah has prepared a great reward for those of you who do good.‚ÄĚ"
  33,30,"O wives of the Prophet! If any of you were to commit a blatant misconduct, the punishment would be doubled for her. And that is easy for Allah"
  33,31,"And whoever of you devoutly obeys Allah and His Messenger and does good, We will grant her double the reward, and We have prepared for her an honourable provision"
  33,32,"O wives of the Prophet! You are not like any other women: if you are mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, then do not be overly effeminate in speech ňĻwith menňļ or those with sickness in their hearts may be tempted, but speak in a moderate tone"
  33,33,"Settle in your homes, and do not display yourselves as women did in the days of ňĻpre-Islamicňļ ignorance. Establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and obey Allah and His Messenger. Allah only intends to keep ňĻthe causes ofňļ evil away from you and purify you completely, O members of the ňĻProphet‚Äôsňļ family"
  33,34,"ňĻAlwaysňļ remember what is recited in your homes of Allah‚Äôs revelations and ňĻpropheticňļ wisdom.¬†Surely Allah is Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  33,35,"Surely ňĻforňļ Muslim men and women, believing men and women,¬†devout men and women, truthful men and women, patient men and women, humble men and women, charitable men and women, fasting men and women, men and women who guard their chastity, and men and women who remember Allah often‚ÄĒfor ňĻall ofňļ them Allah has prepared forgiveness and a great reward"
  33,36,"It is not for a believing man or woman‚ÄĒwhen Allah and His Messenger decree a matter‚ÄĒto have any other choice in that matter.¬†Indeed, whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger has clearly gone ňĻfarňļ astray"
  33,37,"And ňĻremember, O Prophet,ňļ when you said to the one¬†for whom Allah has done a favour and you ňĻtooňļ have done a favour,¬†‚ÄúKeep your wife and fear Allah,‚ÄĚ while concealing within yourself what Allah was going to reveal. And ňĻsoňļ you were considering the people, whereas Allah was more worthy of your consideration. So when Zaid totally lost interest in ňĻkeepingňļ his wife, We gave her to you in marriage, so that there would be no blame on the believers for marrying the ex-wives of their adopted sons after their divorce. And Allah‚Äôs command is totally binding"
  33,38,There is no blame on the Prophet for doing what Allah has ordained for him. That has been the way of Allah with those ňĻprophetsňļ who had gone before. And Allah‚Äôs command has been firmly decreed
  33,39,"ňĻThat is His way withňļ those ňĻprophetsňļ who deliver the messages of Allah, and consider Him, and none but Allah. And sufficient is Allah as a ňĻvigilantňļ Reckoner"
  33,40,"MuŠł•ammad is not the father of any of your men,¬†but is the Messenger of Allah and the seal of the prophets. And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  33,41,O believers! Always remember Allah often
  33,42,and glorify Him morning and evening
  33,43,He is the One Who showers His blessings upon you‚ÄĒand His angels pray for you‚ÄĒso that He may bring you out of darkness and into light. For He is ever Merciful to the believers
  33,44,"Their greeting on the Day they meet Him will be, ‚ÄúPeace!‚ÄĚ And He has prepared for them an honourable reward"
  33,45,"O Prophet! We have sent you as a witness, and a deliverer of good news, and a warner"
  33,46,"and a caller to ňĻthe Way ofňļ Allah by His command, and a beacon of light"
  33,47,Give good news to the believers that they will have a great bounty from Allah
  33,48,"Do not yield to the disbelievers and the hypocrites. Overlook their annoyances, and put your trust in Allah. For Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  33,49,"O believers! If you marry believing women and then divorce them before you touch them,¬†they will have no waiting period for you to count,¬†so give them a ňĻsuitableňļ compensation, and let them go graciously"
  33,50,"O Prophet! We have made lawful for you your wives to whom you have paid their ňĻfullňļ dowries as well as those ňĻbondwomenňļ in your possession, whom Allah has granted you.¬†And ňĻyou are allowed to marryňļ the daughters of your paternal uncles and aunts, and the daughters of your maternal uncles and aunts, who have emigrated like you. Also ňĻallowed for marriage isňļ a believing woman who offers herself to the Prophet ňĻwithout dowryňļ if he is interested in marrying her‚ÄĒňĻthis isňļ exclusively for you, not for the rest of the believers.¬†We know well what ňĻrulingsňļ We have ordained for the believers in relation to their wives and those ňĻbondwomenňļ in their possession. As such, there would be no blame on you. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,51,"It is up to you ňĻO Prophetňļ to delay or receive whoever you please of your wives. There is no blame on you if you call back any of those you have set aside.¬†That is more likely that they will be content, not grieved, and satisfied with what you offer them all. Allah ňĻfullyňļ knows what is in your hearts. And Allah is All-Knowing, Most Forbearing"
  33,52,"It is not lawful for you ňĻO Prophetňļ to marry more women after this, nor can you replace any of your present wives with another, even if her beauty may attract you‚ÄĒexcept those ňĻbondwomenňļ in your possession. And Allah is ever Watchful over all things"
  33,53,"O believers! Do not enter the homes of the Prophet without permission ňĻand if invitedňļ for a meal, do not ňĻcome too early andňļ linger until the meal is ready. But if you are invited, then enter ňĻon timeňļ. Once you have eaten, then go on your way, and do not stay for casual talk. Such behaviour is truly annoying to the Prophet, yet he is too shy to ask you to leave. But Allah is never shy of the truth. And when you ňĻbelieversňļ ask his wives for something, ask them from behind a barrier. This is purer for your hearts and theirs. And it is not right for you to annoy the Messenger of Allah, nor ever marry his wives after him. This would certainly be a major offence in the sight of Allah"
  33,54,"Whether you reveal something or conceal it, surely Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  33,55,"There is no blame on the Prophet‚Äôs wives ňĻif they appear unveiledňļ before their fathers,¬†their sons, their brothers, their brothers‚Äô sons, their sisters‚Äô sons, their fellow ňĻMuslimňļ women, and those ňĻbondspeopleňļ in their possession. And be mindful of Allah ňĻO wives of the Prophet!ňļ Surely Allah is a Witness over all things"
  33,56,"Indeed, Allah showers His blessings upon the Prophet, and His angels pray for him. O believers! Invoke Allah‚Äôs blessings upon him, and salute him with worthy greetings of peace"
  33,57,Surely those who offend Allah¬†and His Messenger¬†are condemned by Allah in this world and the Hereafter. And He has prepared for them a humiliating punishment
  33,58,"As for those who abuse believing men and women¬†unjustifiably, they will definitely bear the guilt of slander and blatant sin"
  33,59,"O Prophet! Ask your wives, daughters, and believing women to draw their cloaks over their bodies. In this way it is more likely that they will be recognized ňĻas virtuousňļ and not be harassed. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,60,"If the hypocrites, and those with sickness in their hearts, and rumour-mongers in Medina do not desist, We will certainly incite you ňĻO Prophetňļ against them, and then they will not be your neighbours there any longer"
  33,61,"ňĻThey deserve to beňļ condemned. ňĻIf they were to persist,ňļ they would get themselves seized and killed relentlessly wherever they are found"
  33,62,That was Allah‚Äôs way with those ňĻhypocritesňļ who have gone before. And you will find no change in Allah‚Äôs way
  33,63,"People ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about the Hour. Say, ‚ÄúThat knowledge is only with Allah. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near.‚ÄĚ"
  33,64,"Surely Allah condemns the disbelievers, and has prepared for them a blazing Fire"
  33,65,to stay there for ever and ever‚ÄĒnever will they find any protector or helper
  33,66,"On the Day their faces are ňĻconstantlyňļ flipped in the Fire, they will cry, ‚ÄúOh! If only we had obeyed Allah and obeyed the Messenger!‚ÄĚ"
  33,67,"And they will say, ‚ÄúOur Lord! We obeyed our leaders and elite, but they led us astray from the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  33,68,"Our Lord! Give them double ňĻourňļ punishment, and condemn them tremendously.‚ÄĚ"
  33,69,"O believers! Do not be like those who slandered Moses, but Allah cleared him of what they said. And he was honourable in the sight of Allah"
  33,70,"O believers! Be mindful of Allah, and say what is right"
  33,71,"He will bless your deeds for you, and forgive your sins. And whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger, has truly achieved a great triumph"
  33,72,"Indeed, We offered the trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they ňĻallňļ declined to bear it, being fearful of it. But humanity assumed it, ňĻforňļ they are truly wrongful ňĻto themselvesňļ and ignorant ňĻof the consequencesňļ"
  33,73,"so that Allah will punish hypocrite men and women and polytheistic men and women, and Allah will turn in mercy to believing men and women. For Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"